From michalsharabi at gmail.com  Mon Sep  5 09:51:01 2016
From: michalsharabi at gmail.com (michal sharabi)
Date: Mon, 05 Sep 2016 07:51:01 +0000
Subject: [Bioc-devel] ctsGE new package for clustering time series data
Message-ID: <CACZORpTkNOaBdKDbCqjJFo4jN-Ysy36pP4sMssDiT8oVM0DdEA@mail.gmail.com>

ctsGE Package:

ctsGE is a package that performs clustering of time-series gene-expression
data: the clustering is done in two steps. First an expression index (i.e.,
a sequence of 1,-1, and 0) is defined that divides genes into groups
according to their expression profiles, and then genes with the same index
are clustered by applying K-means. The ctsGE package also provides an
interactive tool to visualize and explore the gene-expression patterns and
their subclusters.

Regards,
Michal

