You need to bump the 'z' of the x.y.z version when you check in (svn log
shows no version bump). This increment is a trigger for the package to
be (re)built and propagated to the landing page.

Currently the builds run Saturday, Monday and Wednesday at 7:15 pm PST.
Reports are generated about 32 hours later (Mon, Wed, Fri) around 3 am
PST. Whether or not you made your commit before the cutoff will
determine if your changes are seen in the next build report.

More information about version bumping and the version scheme:
http://www.bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/source-control/
http://www.bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/version-numbering/

Valerie

